# 🛑 Reentrancy in emergencyWithdraw

## Severity
High

---

## Description
The `emergencyWithdraw` function does not implement a reentrancy guard and performs an external call before updating the internal state.

This allows control to be transferred to an external contract before the user's balance is reset.

---

## Vulnerable Code

```solidity
function emergencyWithdraw() public {
    payable(msg.sender).call{value: balance[msg.sender]}("");
    balance[msg.sender] = 0;
}



##Impact

A malicious contract can exploit this vulnerability by re-entering the emergencyWithdraw function multiple times before the balance is updated, allowing repeated withdrawals and potentially draining the contract.

## Recommendation

Apply the Checks-Effects-Interactions pattern:
Update state before external calls
Add a reentrancy guard modifier

##Fixed Version

function emergencyWithdraw() public noReentrant {
    uint amount = balance[msg.sender];
    balance[msg.sender] = 0;

    payable(msg.sender).call{value: amount}("");
}






